excerpt: Popular option known for its beachfront location, surf 'n' turf, tiki vibe & umbrella drinks.
detail_description: Duke's Waikiki is a popular beachfront restaurant with a tiki vibe and lively atmosphere, located facing Waikiki's famous Canoes surf break. Named after Duke Kahanamoku, the father of modern surfing, the casual spot offers a variety of appetizers, a large salad bar, and crowd-pleasing entrees such as fish and prime rib. The venue also features memorabilia honoring Duke Kahanamoku and serves the famous Hula Pie dessert.
name: Duke's Waikiki

excerpt: Featuring globally accented, modern Vietnamese cooking in a lively setting with communal tables.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Honolulu's Chinatown, The Pig and The Lady is a must-visit for anyone craving modern Vietnamese cuisine with a twist. This family-run gem offers an exciting menu that changes regularly, showcasing inventive dishes that are rich in flavor and creativity. One standout item is their famous pho French dip sandwich, which has garnered rave reviews for its unique combination of braised brisket and Thai basil chimichurri, served alongside a comforting bowl of pho broth perfect for dipping.
name: The Pig and The Lady
address: 83 N King St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Simple restaurant specializing in local classics such as kalua pork, lomi salmon, and ribs.
detail_description: Helena's Hawaiian Food is a beloved restaurant in Honolulu, serving up traditional Hawaiian dishes since 1946. The casual setting and simple menu allow the focus to be on the delicious food, including kalua pork, lomi salmon, pipikaula (quick ribs), and squid luau. This family-run gem has received accolades such as the James Beard Americas Classics award in 2000 for its authentic regional cuisine.
name: Helena's Hawaiian Food
address: 1240 N School St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Celeb chef Lee Anne Wong runs this brunch stop for breakfast udon, congee & other Pan-Asian eats.
detail_description: Koko Head Cafe, located in Kaimuki, Honolulu, is a popular brunch spot run by celebrity chef Lee Anne Wong. The menu offers a fusion of Asian and Hawaiian flavors with creative dishes like breakfast udon and congee. One of the highlights is the Koko Moco, featuring a medium-rare beef patty on crispy garlic rice with mushroom gravy, a sunny side egg, and kimchi tempura.
name: Koko Head Cafe

excerpt: Local fixture since 1952 for malasadas (Portuguese donuts), breads, pastries & other sweets.
detail_description: Leonard's Bakery has been a beloved local establishment since 1952, renowned for its malasadas, Portuguese donuts that are slightly crispier and chewier than traditional doughnuts. The bakery's influence extends beyond Hawaii, with franchises in Japan. Visitors can savor these delectable treats at scenic locations on the island during guided tours or simply stop by the bakery to indulge in a variety of flavors, from classic custard-filled to tropical-inspired options.
name: Leonard's Bakery

excerpt: Elevated Hawaiian & New American menus, with imaginative drinks, served in refined surrounds.
detail_description: Senia is a highly acclaimed restaurant in Honolulu, offering both Hawaiian and New American cuisine in an elegant setting. The establishment was founded by Chris Kajioka and Anthony Rush, former Per Se alums, who have created a unique dining experience. Guests can choose from a diverse menu featuring modern American small plates, pastas, and large-format platters in the main dining area or opt for the luxurious $185-per-person tasting menu at the 12-seat chef's counter.
name: Senia
address: 75 N King St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Upscale, ocean-front Royal Hawaiian spot for local seafood, with Spanish-Moorish decor & cabanas.
detail_description: Azure is an upscale, ocean-front restaurant located at the Royal Hawaiian with Spanish-Moorish decor and cabanas. The restaurant offers stunning views of Diamond Head and Waikiki Beach, creating a calm island atmosphere. It serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner with a sophisticated evening ambiance. The menu features local seafood, meat, produce, and a chef's multicourse tasting option. Desserts like Russian honey cake and Baked Alaska are also available.
name: Azure

excerpt: Seafood specials, prime rib & jumbo mai tais in a polished, breezy space where sandy feet are okay.
detail_description: Nestled at the base of the Ko'olau Mountains, Haleiwa Joe's Haiku Gardens offers a serene and picturesque setting for both weddings and dining. The venue features beautiful botanical gardens and an open-air Tahitian Chapel, providing dreamy backdrops for intimate ceremonies. Couples can choose from various wedding packages, ranging from minimalist options to comprehensive packages with added services like a ceremony musician and wedding planner.
name: Haleiwa Joe's Haiku Gardens

excerpt: Relaxed beachside venue serving pupu, fish tacos & tropical drinks, plus weekend brunch.
detail_description: Nestled right by the shimmering shores of Waikiki Beach, Hula Grill Waikiki is a delightful plantation-style eatery that offers an inviting atmosphere for both locals and visitors. Situated on the second floor of the Outrigger Waikiki Hotel, this charming venue provides stunning views of Diamond Head and breathtaking sunsets. Whether you're in the mood for a leisurely breakfast featuring fluffy pineapple pancakes or a sumptuous dinner showcasing fresh regional seafood and prime steaks, Hula Grill has something to satisfy every palate.
name: Hula Grill Waikiki

excerpt: Quaint, pint-sized grocery store is a local draw for its counter-serve shave ice & ice cream.
detail_description: Waiola Shave Ice is a popular local spot in Honolulu known for its counter-serve shave ice and ice cream. The quaint grocery store offers a variety of shave ice flavors, including classic options and new creations. One must-try is the Azuki Bowl, featuring shave ice topped with azuki beans, condensed milk, and mochi balls. This small snack shop off the side of the road exudes a definite local vibe and is frequented by both locals and visitors alike.
name: Waiola Shave Ice

excerpt: Bakery & diner since 1950, popular for its breakfasts, comfort food & coco puffs.
detail_description: Liliha Bakery, a beloved establishment since 1950, is renowned for its delectable breakfast offerings and comforting dishes. The bakery prides itself on using locally sourced ingredients and crafting all their baked goods from scratch. With its original location on Honolulu's N. Kuakini St., the bakery has expanded to two additional locations due to its immense popularity.
name: Liliha Bakery
address: 515 N Kuakini St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA

excerpt: Shop selling cream pies, cakes, breads & pastries, plus hot sandwiches & plate lunches.
detail_description: Teds Bakery is a beloved establishment on Oahu's North Shore, offering a wide array of delectable treats such as cream pies, cakes, breads, and pastries. Renowned for its legendary chocolate haupia cream pie, this casual eatery provides an authentic Hawaiian dining experience that has captured the hearts of families and visitors alike. Situated at Sunset Beach with ample outdoor seating, patrons can savor their delicious offerings while enjoying the refreshing breeze from the famous Northern Coast.
name: Ted's Bakery

excerpt: Locals flock to this no-frills eatery for the variety of ahi poke & a chill, laid-back atmosphere.
detail_description: Ono Seafood is a popular no-frills eatery known for its variety of ahi poke and laid-back atmosphere. The owner, Judy Samuka, is renowned for making some of the best poke on the island. The menu offers classic local favorites with made-to-order poke featuring buttery soft ahi and tender tako flavored with various options like shoyu, miso, sea salt, or wasabi.
name: Ono Seafood

excerpt: Classic steakhouse offering prime cuts, seafood & tableside service in an elegant setting.
detail_description: Hy's Steak House is a quintessential dining destination that has shaped the steakhouse experience in Canada and has become a beloved establishment in Hawaii over its impressive 45-year history. Nestled within an elegant setting adorned with aristocratic English-style library decor, this classic steakhouse specializes in USDA Prime Beef, expertly broiled over kiawe wood for an unforgettable flavor.
name: Hy's Steak House

excerpt: A stylish spot for artisan Kona coffee and b. patisserie baked goods.
detail_description: Kona Coffee Purveyors is a stylish destination that offers artisan Kona coffee and delectable baked goods from b. patisserie. Greenwell Farms, situated in the heart of Hawaii's Kona Coffee Belt, has been a pioneer in the industry since its first award at the Vienna Worlds Expo in 1873. The farm is committed to producing top-quality 100% Kona Coffee with various flavor profiles, adhering to world gourmet standards. Meanwhile, b.
name: Kona Coffee Purveyors
address: Kuhio Mall Entrance, 2330 Kalākaua Ave, Honolulu, HI 96815, USA

excerpt: A trendy, colorful hotel bar turning out innovative Hawaiian plates and cocktails next to a pool.
detail_description: Mahina & Sun’s is a lively and trendy hotel bar located in The Surfjack Hotel & Swim Club, drawing both locals and tourists to its vibrant atmosphere. The bar boasts a cool, midcentury aesthetic with nods to 1960s Hawaiian surf culture, featuring custom work by local artisans. The menu offers innovative Hawaiian plates and craft cocktails, including the popular Lavender Rub and daily Market Special.
name: Mahina & Sun’s

excerpt: Chic, glass-walled dining room & terrace with bay views, serving creative meat & seafood dishes.
detail_description: 53 By The Sea is a stylish restaurant located in Honolulu, offering stunning bay views from its glass-walled dining room and terrace. Situated in a McVilla designed to attract Japanese wedding clientele, this establishment serves contemporary Continental cuisine with an emphasis on beautifully presented meat and seafood dishes. The crescent-shaped dining room provides breathtaking ocean views, making it an ideal spot for a romantic date night or upscale happy hour at the bar.
name: 53 By The Sea

excerpt: Fans line up for shave ice in exotic flavors & combos, plus ice cream, at this local institution.
detail_description: Matsumoto Shave Ice is a must-visit local institution on the North Shore, known for its exotic flavors and creative combinations. Visitors often line up to savor the legendary shave ice, which can be found in Haleiwa. The affordable prices and refreshing taste make it a popular choice among tourists exploring the area's attractions like Hukilau Market and Polynesian Cultural Centre.
name: Matsumoto Shave Ice

excerpt: The Sheraton's posh, beachside lounge known for unique cocktails, comfort food & coveted fire pits.
detail_description: RumFire, located at The Royal Hawaiian Hotel in Waikiki, is a luxurious beachside lounge offering stunning views of the water, Diamond Head, and sunset. During the day, guests can relax indoors or outdoors by the fire pits while sipping on cocktails featuring local Hawaiian flavors. The bar also hosts Spiked Afternoon Tea daily from 1-4pm. With a menu boasting around 80 rums organized by their countries of origin, RumFire is a haven for rum enthusiasts.
name: RumFire

excerpt: Simple & snug counter serve providing market-fresh takes on poke bowls inside Kekaulike Market.
detail_description: Maguro Brothers Hawaii Chinatown is a cozy counter-serve spot located in Kekaulike Market, offering market-fresh variations of poke bowls. The establishment is known for its emphasis on fresh fish and minimal seasonings, allowing the quality of the ingredients to shine. Run by experienced brothers from Tsukiji Fish Market in Japan, it's a seafood lover's paradise with offerings like Omakase 7 cuts of Sashimi and Maguro Kama Teriyaki.
name: Maguro Brothers Hawaii Chinatown
address: Maunakea Market Foodcourt, 1120 Maunakea St, Honolulu, HI 96817, USA
